<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2019-11-28</DATELINE><TITLE>Candida auris: A Review of Recommendations for Detection and Control in Healthcare Settings</TITLE><BODY>Candida auris is an emerging multidrug-resistant fungal pathogen. Since first reported in 2009, C. auris has caused healthcare outbreaks around the world, often involving high mortality. Identification of C. auris has been a major challenge as many common conventional laboratory methods cannot accurately detect it. Early detection and implementation of infection control practices can prevent its spread. The aim of this review is to describe recommendations for the detection and control of C. auris in healthcare settings.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>